The paper discusses cognitive radio methodologies for increasing the throughput of wireless systems, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also explores control strategies for managing interference, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses optimizing the transmission policy for the secondary user, which involves system optimization and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on the quality of service, which is a topic in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
